# Python script to automatically generate the Obsidian vault structure based on the architectural plan. This implementation establishes a two-level "controlled hierarchy" to minimize cognitive load [1] and includes pre-configured templates for atomic notes, interview preparation, and technical laboratories.[2, 3]
The vault is organized into the following key zones:
10 - MOCs (Maps of Content): Centralized indices to navigate broad domains like Cloud Security or Networking.
20 - Key Concepts: Atomic technical notes with standardized metadata for encryption and protocol security.[2, 4]
30 - Interviews: A repository for STAR-method responses and technical Q&A, including networking fundamentals and cloud-native security.
99 - Meta: A storage area for templates and automation scripts, such as MITRE ATT&CK parsers.

